ssinsider.com%20(Pete%20Syme)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A27%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fflying-taxi-firm-archer-gets-faa-approval-for-commercial-operations-2024-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I'm%20an%20ex-Google%20recruiter%20and%20head%20of%20talent%20at%20DoorDash.%20PIPs%20should%20stand%20for%20'paid%20interview%20period'%20%E2%80%94%20if%20you're%20put%20on%20one%2C%20get%20out%20fast.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222400%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Nolan%20Church%20headshot.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66607868d0b8e1c832cc18ed%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221800%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%20Nolan%20Church%20is%20the%20cofounder%20and%20CEO%20of%20FairComp%20and%20Continuum.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Nolan%20Church%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ENolan%20Church%20was%20the%20former%20head%20of%20talent%20at%20DoorDash%20and%20ex-chief%20people%20officer%20at%20Carta.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20said%20companies%20use%20PIPs%20to%20protect%20themselves%20and%20avoid%20blindsiding%20employees%20with%20firings.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EChurch%20said%20if%20you're%20put%20on%20a%20PIP%20you've%20been%C2%A0%26quot%3Bscarlet-lettered%26quot%3B%20and%20should%20move%20jobs%20immediately.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20transcribed%20conversation%20with%20Nolan%20Church%2C%20a%20former%20recruiter%20at%20Google%20and%20DoorDash%20and%20ex-chief%20people%20officer%20at%20Carta%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cstrong%3E%2C%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%20about%20his%20experience%20of%20putting%20people%20on%20PIPs.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20spent%20my%20career%20in%20recruitment.%20From%20May%202012%20to%20early%202015%2C%20I%20worked%20as%20a%20recruiter%20for%20Google%20Access.%20Then%2C%20I%20became%20the%20head%20of%20recruiting%20at%20DoorDash%20and%20later%20the%20chief%20people%20officer%20at%20Carta%2C%20a%20pre-IPO%20equity%20management%20company%20for%20startups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22db049f1c-23fc-4ffd-a015-73387ecc996f%5C%22%3EMy%20first%20experience%20with%20PIPs%20was%20at%20DoorDash%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDoorDash%20was%20the%20first%20place%20I%20encountered%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fperformance-improvement-plan-pip-survived-teacher-better-employee-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eperformance%20improvement%20plans%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20PIPs.%20They're%20a%20way%20of%20giving%20a%20low%20performer%20a%20chance%20to%20correct%20a%20performance%20problem%20before%20termination.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20joined%20as%20the%20head%20of%20talent%20in%20March%202015%2C%20I%20was%20the%20company's%2050th%20employee.%20This%20was%20a%20key%20leadership%20role%20for%20HR%20and%20recruiting.%20We%20were%20setting%20a%20company%20precedent%20for%20how%20we%20wanted%20to%20manage%20our%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20we%20started%20encountering%20low%20performers%2C%20we%20needed%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20to%20manage%20them.%20So%20we%20talked%20to%20former%20or%20current%20heads%20of%20HR%20at%20other%20companies%20to%20understand%20how%20they%20thought%20about%20performance%20management.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20said%20there%20were%20two%20ways%20that%20companies%20thought%20about%20PIPs%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0do%20them%20or%20don't.%20The%20HR%20leaders%20said%20we%20could%20either%20make%20it%20so%20everyone%20went%20on%20a%20PIP%20before%20being%20terminated%20or%20put%20no%20one%20on%20a%20PIP%20and%20give%20increasing%20feedback%20to%20lower%20performers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20went%20the%20PIP%20route%20at%20DoorDash.%20In%20the%20early%20days%2C%20we%20decided%20that%20the%20sales%20team%20would%20be%20the%20only%20team%20with%20a%20formal%20PIP%20process%20because%20they%20were%20the%20department%20with%20the%20clearest%20metrics.%20It's%20You're%20either%20hitting%20your%20quota%20or%20you're%20not.%20Sales%20metrics%20are%20very%20black%20and%20white.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20could%20be%20very%20clear%20with%20somebody%20and%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20don't%20hit%20quota%2C%20this%20is%20going%20to%20be%20your%20last%20month%20of%20employment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20my%20tenure%2C%20everybody%20I%20saw%20being%20put%20on%20a%20PIP%20got%20terminated%20either%20during%20the%20PIP%20or%20shortly%20after.%20My%20personal%20take%20is%20that%20once%20you%20get%20to%20the%20point%20of%20putting%20somebody%20on%20a%20PIP%2C%20the%20decision%20to%20terminate%20has%20already%20been%20made.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229f1096c8-dc64-4fda-b2c5-650d1d85b9af%5C%22%3EI've%20never%20seen%20someone%20survive%20a%20PIP%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20moved%20to%20Carta%20in%202018%20as%20the%20chief%20people%20officer%2C%20we%20had%20a%20lot%20of%20discussions%20there%20about%20whether%20we%20wanted%20to%20put%20people%20on%20PIPs.%20Early%20on%2C%20I%20instituted%20a%20policy%20that%20required%20managers%20to%20put%20employees%20on%20a%20PIP%20before%20terminating.%20We%20did%20this%20to%20ensure%20managers%20delivered%20feedback%20and%20employees%20weren't%20surprised%20they%20were%20being%20let%20go.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20as%20we%20put%20people%20on%20PIPs%2C%20we%20found%20them%20to%20be%20disingenuous%20and%20ultimately%20eliminated%20them.%20Instead%2C%20we%20terminated%20employees%20with%20a%20generous%20severance%20package.%20To%20be%20candid%2C%20I've%20never%20seen%20somebody%20survive%20a%20PIP.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20company%2C%20you%20want%20to%20consider%20why%20you're%20putting%20someone%20on%20a%20PIP.%20Are%20you%20doing%20it%20to%20make%20the%20employee%20successful%3F%20Or%20to%20cover%20your%20ass%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPIPs%20are%20used%20by%20companies%20to%20cover%20their%20ass%20almost%20every%20single%20time%20because%20a%20team%20doesn't%20have%20enough%20data%20about%20performance%2C%20and%20managers%20don't%20do%20a%20great%20job%20of%20providing%20feedback.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUsually%2C%20companies%20put%20someone%20on%20a%20PIP%20because%20they're%20worried%20that%20the%20employee%20will%20be%20surprised%20by%20their%20termination%20without%20one%20and%20could%20take%20legal%20action.%20The%20PIP%20provides%20legal%20cover.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22436ca7e0-e6d7-427d-8ebc-4ca6c298ab00%5C%22%3EIf%20you%20get%20put%20on%20a%20PIP%2C%20make%20the%20acronym%20stand%20for%20Paid%20Interview%20Period%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20an%20employee%20on%20a%20PIP%2C%20you%20need%20to%20view%20it%20not%20as%20a%20%26quot%3BPerformance%20Improvement%20Plan%26quot%3B%20but%20as%20a%20%26quot%3BPaid%20Interview%20Period%26quot%3B%20because%20your%20employment%20is%20coming%20to%20an%20end%20at%20that%20company%2C%20either%20very%20shortly%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20PIP%20or%20usually%20soon%20thereafter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20should%20assume%20it's%20not%20worked%20out%20at%20that%20company%20and%20put%20the%20majority%20of%20your%20efforts%20into%20trying%20to%20find%20a%20new%20job%20as%20fast%20as%20possible.%20Even%20if%20you%20survive%20the%20PIP%2C%20you%20have%20to%20think%20about%20%26quot%3Bwhat%20happens%20to%20me%20now%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20a%20very%20large%20community%20of%20HR%20leaders%20in%20my%20circle.%20I've%20never%20heard%20of%20somebody%20who%20went%20on%20a%20PIP%20and%20became%20a%20top%20performer%20at%20that%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20even%20if%20you%20survive%2C%20you've%20been%20scarlet-lettered%20at%20that%20company.%20The%20likelihood%20of%20you%20getting%20a%20raise%20or%20promotion%20after%20a%20PIP%20is%20insanely%20low.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20best%20option%20for%20you%20is%20to%20find%20a%20different%20company%20where%20you%20can%20be%20successful%20and%20start%20with%20a%20clean%20slate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20origi