sed%20and%20weaponized%20by%20bad%20actors.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20really%20a%20precedent%20in%20social%20media%20for%20regulation%2C%20and%20doing%20it%20sooner%20rather%20than%20later%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Pasquale.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESurden%20argued%20that%20the%20early%20discussions%20regarding%20the%20regulation%20of%20social%20media%20%26quot%3Blargely%20failed%20to%20predict%20other%20main%20issues%20about%20social%20media%20that%20we%20are%20worried%20about%20today%20that%20many%20today%20consider%20to%20be%20more%20significant.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20includes%20how%20social%20media%20affects%20youth's%20mental%20health%20and%20the%20propagation%20of%20disinformation%20and%20misinformation%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20noted%20that%20the%20ability%20to%20regulate%20social%20media%20today%20exists%2C%20but%20that%20it's%20not%20clear%20what%20the%20effective%20legal%20solutions%20are%20for%20the%20societal%20problems%20that%20have%20arisen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%2C%20as%20a%20society%2C%20are%20not%20often%20as%20accurate%20at%20predicting%20issues%20ahead%20of%20time%20as%20we%20like%20to%20think%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Surden.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20there%20is%20a%20similar%20lesson%20about%20AI%20%E2%80%94%20we%20can%20certainly%20see%20issues%20of%20today%20that%20we%20need%20to%20be%20careful%20about%2C%20including%20privacy%2C%20bias%2C%20accuracy%2C%26quot%3B%20Surden%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20we%20should%20be%20humble%20about%20our%20ability%20to%20predict%20and%20preemptively%20regulate%20AI%20technology%20problems%20ahead%20of%20time%20as%20we%20are%20often%20quite%20bad%20about%20predicting%20the%20details%20or%20the%20societal%20impacts.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-new-dark-age-risks-regulations-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1717668002000%2C%22visual