201.5%20kg%20of%20%3Cem%3Ebesan%3C%2Fem%3E%20(chickpea%20flour)%20and%20jaggery%20each.%20Fill%20the%20water%20to%20the%20rim%20and%20stir%20the%20mixture.%20Take%2040%20litres%20of%20%3Cem%3Ejivamrit%20%3C%2Fem%3Eto%20fertilise%20one%20%3Cem%3Ebigha%20%3C%2Fem%3Eof%20land%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Ranjit%20shares%20his%20secrets%20to%20preparing%20natural%20insecticides%20such%20as%20%3Cem%3Ebrahmastra%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%20%3Cem%3Eagnihastra%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethat%20enhance%20plant%20disease%20resistance%2C%20provide%20nutrients%2C%20and%20control%20insects.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTo%20make%20%3Cem%3Ebrahmastra%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Etake%20one%20kg%20of%20four%20kinds%20of%20leaves%20and%20neem.%20Crush%20them%20and%20add%20in%20four%20litres%20of%20cow%20urine%20and%20dung.%20Boil%20the%20mixture.%20After%20two%20boils%2C%20cool%20it%20down%20and%20strain%20it%20into%20a%20tank.%20It%20will%20be%20ready%20to%20be%20sprayed%20on%20crops%20after%2048%20hours.%20You%20can%20also%20store%20this%20insecticide%20for%20six%20months%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F05%2Fhimachal-1-1717133339.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20couple%20makes%20their%20own%20natural%20fertilisers%20using%20simple%20ingredients%20like%20cow%20dung%20and%20urine.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F05%2Fhimachal-1-1717133339.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F05%2Fhimachal-1-1717133339-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F05%2Fhimachal-1-1717133339-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F05%2Fhimachal-1-1717133339-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F05%2Fhimachal-1-1717133339-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-351655%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20couple%20makes%20their%20own%20natural%20fertilisers%20using%20simple%20ingredients%20like%20cow%20dung%20and%20urine.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20insects%20are%20still%20not%20controlled%2C%20we%20use%20our%20%3Cem%3Eagnihastra.%20%3C%2Fem%3EIt%20is%20prepared%20using%20spicy%20green%20chillies%2C%20peppers%2C%20and%20garlic.%20It%20is%20sure%20to%20control%20pest%20attacks%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJaswinder%20points%20out%2C%20%E2%80%9CIn%20addition%20to%20the%20natural%20fertilisers%2C%20ensure%20to%20make%20the%20%3Cem%3Emedh%20%3C%2Fem%3E(field%20boundary)%20wall%20higher%20so%20that%20chemical%20water%20from%20neighbouring%20fields%20does%20not%20seep%20into%20your%20soil.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20the%20couple%20has%20received%20immense%20recognition%20for%20their%20work.%20In%20April%20this%20year%2C%20they%20were%20awarded%20by%20the%20Agriculture%20University%20of%20Sirmour.%20On%20the%20occasion%20of%20the%20International%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Day%20in%202022%2C%20they%20were%20honoured%20by%20the%20Deputy%20Commissioner%20of%20Sirmaur%2C%20IAS%20Sumit%20Khimta.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20small%20farmers%20who%20are%20receiving%20so%20much%20recognition.%20It%20is%20a%20big%20achievement%20for%20us.%20We%20never%20knew%20we%20would%20get%20opportunities%20to%20address%20thousands%20of%20people%20in%20front%20of%20the%20officials%20like%20the%20governor%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Jaswinder.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20than%20recognition%2C%20Jaswinder%20takes%20pride%20in%20receiving%20compliments%20from%20her%20guests.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEarlier%2C%20if%20I%20ignored%20the%20%3Cem%3Ephulke%20%3C%2Fem%3E(wheat%20chapati)%20for%20some%20time%2C%20they%20would%20harden%20and%20dry%20out.%20But%20those%20prepared%20from%20the%20naturally%20grown%20wheat%20remain%20soft.%20We%20get%20lots%20of%20praise%20from%20guests%20for%20the%20taste%20and%20aroma%20of%20our%20chapati%20and%20vegetables.%20When%20asked%2C%20we%20tell%20them%20the%20magic%20behind%20it%20is%20natural%20farming!%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Padmashree%20Pande.%20All%20photos%3A%20Ranjit%20Singh.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1717146517000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F05%2Fhimachal-2-1717133412.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D351525%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22For%20the%20past%20six%20years%2C%20Jaswinder%20Kaur%20and%20Ranjit%20Singh%20from%20Himachal%20have%20been%20using%20zero-budget%20natural%20farming%20to%20cultivate%20at%20least%2025%20kinds%20of%20crops.%20Here's%20how%20they%20made%20farming%20profitable%20and%20train%20others%20around%20them.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Shivani%20Gupta%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F351525%2Ffarming-profitable-how-to-make-natural-pesticides-himachal-couple-zero-budget-natural-earns-double%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Why%20Gardening%3F%20%E2%80%98It%20Helped%20Channel%20My%20Grief%20After%20I%20Lost%20My%20Dad%E2%80%99%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EMayank%20Sharma%E2%80%99s%20apartment%20terrace%20in%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20Vikas%20Puri%20is%20a%20cross%20between%20a%20forest%2C%20a%20garden%20and%20a%20passion%20project.%20Just%20as%20you%20think%20the%20place%20has%20revealed%20all%20its%20surprises%2C%20you%20turn%20a%20corner%20to%20find%20out%20you%20were%20wrong.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPumpkins%2C%20cherry%20tomatoes%2C%20beetroot%20and%20broccoli%20grace%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebe